ir bin Abdullah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was on a journey and he saw a crowd of people over a man being shaded by them. The Prophet said, \"What is this?\" They said, \"He is fasting.\" The Prophet said, \"It is not righteousness\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25415,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/13\/salat-shortened-two-rakaat-travel\/","url_meta":{"origin":15496,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Prayer shortened to two cycles during travel","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 13, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: I accompanied the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and during travel he would not add more to his prayer than two cycles. Abu Bakr, Umar, and Uthman did likewise, may Allah be pleased with them. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1051, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 689 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31753,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/03\/two-rakaat-after-travel\/","url_meta":{"origin":15496,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Praying two cycles upon return from a journey","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 3, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ka\u2019b reported: When the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, returned home in the forenoon after a journey, he would enter the mosque and pray two cycles before sitting down. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 2922, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 716 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25400,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/09\/combine-salat-traveling\/","url_meta":{"origin":15496,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Travel: The Prophet combined prayers during travel","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 9, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, combined sunset and evening\u00a0prayers if he was undertaking a journey. And Ibn Abbas said, \u201cThe Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, combined the noon prayers and afternoon prayers\u00a0if he was on a journey, as well as\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15502,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/29\/dua-returning-travel-journey\/","url_meta":{"origin":15496,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Dua: The Prophet\u2019s supplication for coming home","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 29, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: Abu Talha and I returned from a journey along with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and Safiyya rode behind him on his camel. When we reached the outskirts of Medina, the Prophet said, \u201cWe are returning and repenting, worshiping our Lord and praising\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/15496","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=15496"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/15496\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=15496"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=15496"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=15496"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}